        "orario": "13:00",
        "timestamp": 1772798401,
        "contenuto_esteso": "To display this content from YouTube, you must enable advertisement tracking and audience measurement. One of your browser extensions seems to be blocking the video player from loading. To watch this content, you may need to disable it on this site. Conservative Anglicans challenge historic female leader with rival leadership Africa Issued on: 06/03/2026 - 13:00 Conservative Anglican leaders in Nigeria have restructured their organisation signalling a break from the traditions of the historic Anglican Communion. Gafcon leaders have opposed liberal trends such as same-sex marriage, the ordination of openly LGBTQ+ clergy in the Anglican churches of Europe and North America, including the Episcopal Church in the United States and the recent nomination of the Church's first female leader. Mine collapses in eastern Congo, with official death toll disputed by M23 rebels 06/03/2026 Africa Zimbabwe pulls out of US health aid talks 26/02/2026 Africa Ghana FM urges Ukraine to release two Ghanaian POWs 26/02/2026 Africa Senegalese PM Ousmane Sonko submits tougher anti-LGBT law 26/02/2026 Africa How do US tariffs impact South African economy? 24/02/2026 Africa 'If we can get a Coca-Cola to the most remote parts of the world, we can get cooking gas, as well' 18/02/2026 Africa Sudanese people face 'generations of trauma', head of UN OCHA tells France 24 18/02/2026 Africa Security takes centre stage at African Union summit 17/02/2026 Africa AU Summit: Guterres and Youssouf urge action on Sudan, Palestine 15/02/2026 Africa"
