        "contenuto_esteso": "To display this content from YouTube, you must enable advertisement tracking and audience measurement. One of your browser extensions seems to be blocking the video player from loading. To watch this content, you may need to disable it on this site. Middle East conflict threatens food security in Gulf countries Middle East Issued on: 06/03/2026 - 12:29 Sitting between Oman and Iran, the Strait of Hormuz is a crucial global shipping channel with more than 30,000 ships passing through it each year. Following the outbreak of the conflict in the Middle East, concerns have arisen about oil and gas exports through the strait being impacted. But at the same time, the threat of disruption to food supplies in the Gulf region are increasing, as states such as Kuwait, Bahrain and Qatar become effectively landlocked by the disruption. Israeli airstrikes pound Lebanon, displacing hundreds of thousands 06/03/2026 Middle East US likely responsible for Iranian girlschool bombing, says investigation 06/03/2026 Middle East US Congress rejects \"war powers resolution\" that would halt strikes in Iran 06/03/2026 Middle East Donald Trump seeks Kyiv's help in defending against Iranian drones 06/03/2026 Middle East \"There doesn't seem to be a plan in Iran\" for the Trump administation 06/03/2026 Middle East To avoid \"US boots on the ground\", Washington considers enlisting separatists in Iran 06/03/2026 Middle East Israeli strikes on Lebanon: Tel Aviv seeks to 'eliminate Hezbollah' 06/03/2026 Middle East Nadim Houry: Middle East being overrun by 'madmen' showing total disregard for international law 06/03/2026 Middle East Trump urges Iranian diplomats around the world to request asylum 05/03/2026 Middle East"
